Ok, anything else to be done?

I think the pxd-versioning should allow NumPy to start shipping and using the properties from day one, without creating hard dependencies. The only difference between the two versions (Cython/NumPy) that I'm aware of is that the properties in Cython are read-only, whereas the struct fields are writable. The rest should be the same now (AFAICT).

@mattip, do you see anything else that we could do?
